    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "I think the most elegant solution would simply be to put the -Shuffle parameter in a completely different parameter set, so that it can't be used with -Count, via the `Parameter` attribute:\r\n\r\n```csharp\r\n[Parameter(Mandatory = true, ParameterSetName = \"ShuffleSet\")]\r\npublic SwitchParameter Shuffle { get; set; }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen when determining your code path you can use `switch (ParameterSetName)` to determine which code path to take. ðŸ™‚ ",
